Simon Jack speaks to some of those involved including Britain's finance minister at the time Alistair Darling. He asks Professor Kenneth Rogoff if it was a mistake to let Lehman's go bust. And Tony Lomas from auditors PWC explains how some people are making lots of money from picking over Lehman's corpse.
